casebody.data:
Christopher Jay MCCOLLUM, Appellant,
v.
DIRECTOR OF REVENUE, Respondent. WD 81360 Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. ORDER FILED: January 15, 2019 Jeffrey S. Eastman, Gladstone, MO, Attorney for Appellant. Eric Schmitt, Attorney General, and Morgan L. Brewington, Special Assistant Attorney General, Jefferson City, MO, Attorneys for Respondent. Before Division Two: Alok Ahuja, Presiding Judge, and Thomas H. Newton and Mark D. Pfeiffer, Judges

Order

Per Curiam:

Mr. Christopher Jay McCollum appeals from the judgment of the Circuit Court of Platte County, Missouri, upholding the Director of Revenue's suspension of McCollum's driver's license under section 302.505.1 after his arrest for driving a motor vehicle while intoxicated. Because a published opinion would have no precedential value, a memorandum of law has been provided to the parties. The judgment is affirmed. Rule 84.16(b).
